                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-103" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS SLATER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a butcher at Kensington—On the 10th of July I paid the prisoner between 14<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. and 15<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. on his master's account.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAIN</hi>. <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I have my book—here is the entry of the 20th of July of 14<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 5<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., received from Mr. Slater, in the prisoner's hand-writing—he never accounted to me for that—19<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. was left in the cash-bowl—he left me without any notice—the total amount entered that day is about 34<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., but his sister brought me 17<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> When did she bring that? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> On the Monday as this happened on the Saturday—I believe the officer has got 7<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.—his salary was 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. a week.</p>
